 as a Thomasian\nstudent is to seek truth with integrity and let knowledge guide me toward holiness.\n3. After attending the ALAB 2026 UST retreat, what concrete personal actions will you\nundertake to respond to the call of the retreat of \u201cmissionary rekindling\u201d as a Thomasian\nstudent? How do you bear witness to the retreat\u2019s theme, \u201cALAB 2026:\nPananampalataya, Pag-asa, Pag-ibig?\n- I will integrate prayer into my studies, viewing my academic work as a holy pursuit\nof truth and holiness, thereby answering the missionary call. I will practice the\npedagogy of hope by being truly present with classmates, believing in their potential\nso that hope is caught, not just taught. I will intentionally choose to will the good of\nothers, even when feelings fade, allowing love to be refined and endure through\nchallenges, instead of retreating into cynicism. By trusting God's timing over my own\nwishes, I will avoid arrogance and despair. I will embody the ALAB 2026 theme\nletting the fires of truth, love, and hope transform my life by living faith through my\nstudies, hope through companionship, and love through thoughtful choices."}}
