[2026-04-05 01:01:56.085] [PRINT]   "extracted_file_text": "1. What specific key points from the Day 1, 2, and 3 conference talks were most striking to\nyou? Give one concrete learning for each conference talk.\n- The first day's discussion on vocation led to the realization that studying is a sacred\nobligation to find truth and develop holiness, not just to pass exams. Inspired by St.\nThomas Aquinas, I learned that seeking truth requires courage, even if it means\nsacrificing comfort or opposing corruption. The second day broadened my\nunderstanding of love, defining it as the purposeful pursuit of the other person's\nunconditional well-being, persevering through changing emotions and trials. Finally,\nthe third day's mission reflection emphasized that hope is absorbed through\ninspiration and companionship, caught by believing in a person's greatest qualities\nthrough shared experiences.\n2. How did the university retreat help you personally? What aspects of your life you felt the\nretreat became most helpful?\n- The university retreat helped me confront the pessimism that had inadvertently\nseeped into my heart regarding love and relationships. I realized my tendency to\nanticipate failure or shield myself from disappointment was a form of despair,\nimpeding necessary personal development. The retreat also reframed my academic\nlife, helping me view my education as a vocation intertwined with spiritual\ndevelopment, rather than a mere duty. This gave me clarity: my goal as a Thomasian\nstudent is to seek truth with integrity and let knowledge guide me toward holiness.\n3. After attending the ALAB 2026 UST retreat, what concrete personal actions will you\nundertake to respond to the call of the retreat of \u201cmissionary rekindling\u201d as a Thomasian\nstudent? How do you bear witness to the retreat\u2019s theme, \u201cALAB 2026:\nPananampalataya, Pag-asa, Pag-ibig?\n- I will integrate prayer into my studies, viewing my academic work as a holy pursuit\nof truth and holiness, thereby answering the missionary call. I will practice the\npedagogy of hope by being truly present with classmates, believing in their potential\nso that hope is caught, not just taught. I will intentionally choose to will the good of\nothers, even when feelings fade, allowing love to be refined and endure through\nchallenges, instead of retreating into cynicism. By trusting God's timing over my own\nwishes, I will avoid arrogance and despair. I will embody the ALAB 2026 theme\nletting the fires of truth, love, and hope transform my life by living faith through my\nstudies, hope through companionship, and love through thoughtful choices.",
